13 NEW SECTION. Section 1. State shooting complex facilities and improvements development
14 and oversight task force -- membership -- duties -- reporting. (1) There is a state shooting complex facilities
15 and improvements development and oversight task force, which is composed of the following members:
16 (a) the governor or the governor's designee;
17 (b) a member of the board of state parks and recreation or the board member's designee;
18 (c) the director of the department of commerce or the director's designee;
19 (d) two members representing firearm, archery, or firearm accessory manufacturing companies in
20 the state, appointed by the governor;
21 (e) one member of the public representing a shooting sports organization that has representation
22 in the state, appointed by the governor;
23 (f) one member of the public representing a hunting or wildlife conservation organization that is
24 headquartered in the state or that has an active chapter in the state, appointed by the governor;
25 (g) two members of the house of representatives, appointed by the speaker of the house. The
26 speaker of the house shall designate a co-chairperson of the task force.
27 (h) two members of the senate, appointed by the president of the senate. The president of the
