2 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Montana state shooting complex facilities and improvements
3 account. (1) There is a Montana state shooting complex facilities and improvements account in the state
4 special revenue fund established in 17-2-102. The account is administered by the department of commerce
5 fish, wildlife, and parks.
6 (2) Money transferred from a lawful source, including but not limited to gifts, grants, donations,
7 securities, and other assets, public or private, may be deposited in the account.
8 (3) Money in the account may be used only for the siting and construction of the Montana state
9 shooting complex to develop a framework for the selection and location of state-supported shooting facilities,
10 improvements in existing facilities, and funding mechanisms.
11 (4) Interest and income earned on the account and any unspent or unencumbered money in the
12 account at the end of a fiscal year must remain in the account.
13
14 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Appropriation. (1) There is appropriated $55,000 from the general fund
15 to the department of fish, wildlife, and parks for the biennium beginning July 1, 2025, for the purposes
16 described in [section 1].
17 (2) Money from the appropriation that is not spent during the biennium must revert to the general
18 fund.
19
20 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Effective date. [This act] is effective July 1, 2025.
21
22 NEW SECTION. Section 5. Termination. [Section 1] terminates June 30, 2027.
